= Slam Conventions

We do not play two-suit KC.

Our primary KC-asking method is kickback.

In some well defined situations we use plain minorwood or optional
minorwood instead of kickback.

== Minorwood

Applies by an unpassed hand when four of the agreed minor is not
needed as a natural bid.

*Cases:*

@ jump to 4m after minor-suit agreement

@ self raise to 4m following a minor-suit
_ transfer opposite a 1NT opening

@ second-round jump-raise to 4m by #responder#

@ raise by responder after jump rebid by opener

=== Jump to FOUR MINOR after minor-suit agreement

*Conditions* (all required)*:* +
@ we have agreed a minor +
@ we have not agreed a major +
@ the auction is uncontested +
@ #four of the agreed minor is a jump#

