[#_kickback_diamonds_and_hearts]
== Kickback for diamonds when hearts are in focus

The primary issue with kickback is when diamonds are agreed and 4H is
still a possible contract.

4H will be kickback #unless hearts are in focus as a possible contract.#

A major-suit is in focus when one of the following applies:

["lowerroman"]
. it was rebid directly after diamond agreement
. delayed support was given directly after diamond agreement
. it was bid on the first round

=== Diamonds agreed, hearts in focus, at 3D

4D is not a jump, so not minorwood.

A jump to 4H is kickback.

[%autowidth,cols="2*^.^a",grid="none"]
|===
|
[grid="none",stripes="none",frame="allx"]
:===
  1D : 1H
  2C : [nobr]#3D{ensp}GF#
  ?  :
:===
|
[%autowidth,grid="none",stripes="odd",frame="nonex"]
!===
! {D} agreed +
  4D is not a jump +
  > 4D is NOT minorwood +
  4H is a jump +
  > !4H! is kickback
!===
|===

=== Diamonds agreed, hearts in focus, at 3H

After diamonds agreed and hearts offered as a possible trump-suit, then: +

[%autowidth,cols="<",grid="none"]
|===
| a raise of 3H to 4H is an offer to play
| a jump to 4S is kickback for hearts
| 4D indicates: +
  @ no interest in playing in hearts +
  @ nothing more to say
| An unbid suit or 4C reaffirms diamonds as trump
  and shows slam interest +
  > 4H by either player = kickback for diamonds
|===

